{
  "stem": "24346.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, in 1938, Poland changed for the worse regarding anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't remember what this Polish lady, what position she held in the government, Madame-- we used to call her Madame [?",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Prista, ?] [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Pristarova. ?] And she came out with a rule, she convinced the Polish Senate to pass it, that kosher slaughtering is inhumane, and they should limit kosher slaughtering.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That was around 1937 or 1938, be closer-- it was close to the war.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in fact, what they gave, gave the limit that you are allowed to slaughter how many steers or how many cows, there wouldn't be enough meat to go around for the Jewish population.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the Rabbinate, the Jewish Rabbinate passed a law-- the hindquarters were treyf.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You couldn't use them as kosher.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they passed a law that we could [INAUDIBLE], take out the main veins, and they taught people-- menachers, they used to call them-- who used to bone out the meat and take out the veins.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we used the hindquarter also for kosher.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then we had enough.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Of course, poultry, [INAUDIBLE]-- then there was enough meat to go around.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "However, this lady was from the anti-Semitic side.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And to make it look nice-- it's not humane, it's unhumane to slaughter the Jewish style.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Also, they had started putting up signs in Polish stores-- [NON-ENGLISH], meaning, don't buy by the Jew, patronize Polish stores.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Open-- it used to be called Democratic Poland, but it wasn't really democratic.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Huh huh.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It made me feel bad, because I felt I was born in Poland, I'm a Polish citizen like anybody else.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "If it's a democracy, all the citizens should be treated alike.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In fact, that wasn't the case.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, one incident-- this I witnessed.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
